AMPure Bead Purification Protocol

1. Combine 2x volume of beads and 1x volume of sample. Pipette to mix.
2. Incubate at RT for 5 minutes.
3. Place tube onto a magnet for 2 minutes or until clear (keep tube on magnet up to step 10).
4. Remove supernatant.
5. Add 200 uL of newly prepared 80% ethanol and incubate for 1 minute.
6. Remove ethanol.
7. Add 200 uL of 80% ethanol and incubate for 1 minute.
8. Remove ethanol.
9. Let beads dry for 5 minutes.
10. Remove tube from magnet, elute in 30 uL of H2O and pipette to mix.
11. Incubate for 5 minutes. 
12. Place samples back on the magnet and incubate for 2 minutes.
13. Collect eluted DNA and place into a new tube.